    "Background": {
      "text": "Atypical\nMycobacterium\nspecies found in fresh or salt water (cold or warm)\nBacteria that causes \"fish tank Granuloma\"\nCan infect both immunocompetent and immunocompromised hosts\nM. marinum is generally not found in chlorinated swimming pools\n[1]",
      "subsections": {
        "Risk_Factors": {
          "text": "Aquarium workers and enthusiasts\nSwimming\nHandling of contaminated water",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
